oleBinding is defined with proper metadata\n67: - [ ] Verify rules reference .Values.controllerManager.rbac.rules\n68: - [ ] Verify subjects reference correct ServiceAccount\n69: - [ ] Verify roleRef references correct Role\n70: - [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n71: \n72: **Verification**: Template matches delta-spec.md requirements for Controller Manager\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: ### Task 6: Define Controller Manager Role rules in values.yaml\n77: - [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/values.yaml controllerManager.rbac.rules section\n78: - [ ] Define rules for managing AgentCube CRDs (agentruntimes, codeinterpreters)\n79: - [ ] Define rules for watching and updating resources\n80: - [ ] Define rules for creating and managing sub-resources (configmaps, secrets, events)\n81: - [ ] Define rules for status subresources\n82: - [ ] Ensure rules are namespace-scoped (no cluster-wide permissions)\n83: - [ ] Follow principle of least privilege\n84: - [ ] Add rule for getting and updating pods status\n85: - [ ] Add rule for creating events\n86: \n87: **Verification**: Controller Manager Role has all required permissions with minimal privileges\n88: \n89: ---\n90: \n91: ### Task 7: Review existing Router ServiceAccount template\n92: - [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/serviceaccount.yaml\n93: - [ ] Verify template includes proper Helm conditionals\n94: - [ ] Verify template uses correct helper functions\n95: - [ ] Verify component label is set to router\n96: - [ ] Verify annotations are conditionally included\n97: - [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n98: \n99: **Verification**: Template follows best practices and matches component pattern\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ### Task 8: Review existing Router RBAC template\n104: - [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/router/rbac.yaml\n105: - [ ] Verify Role is defined with proper metadata\n106: - [ ] Verify RoleBinding is defined with proper metadata\n107: - [ ] Verify rules i