{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775886947271,"sessionID":"ses_284ea1c7dffeW7xKCHghFbOWeg","part":{"id":"prt_d7b1c531a001YcNwo46gN56C56","messageID":"msg_d7b1a6246001knnZnm7Dmty503","sessionID":"ses_284ea1c7dffeW7xKCHghFbOWeg","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-dea01008aa9c43498956f68d45e41db4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-035 — client-go 类型客户端生成 Delta Specification\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-035\n- **Title**: client-go 类型客户端生成\n- **Module**: client-go\n- **Language**: Go\n- **Size**: L\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for generating a Kubernetes client-go based typed client library for AgentCube custom resources. It defines requirements for client generation, API interfaces, informers, listers, and testing to ensure proper type-safe Kubernetes API access.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Go module initialization and structure\n\nThe system SHALL initialize a Go module with proper structure for the client-go library.\n\n#### Scenario: Go module initialization\n- **GIVEN** a client-go directory is created\n- **WHEN** `go mod init github.com/agentcube/client-go` is executed\n- **THEN** a go.mod file SHALL be created\n- **AND** the module name SHALL be github.com/agentcube/client-go\n- **AND** the Go version SHALL be 1.19 or higher\n\n#### Scenario: Directory structure creation\n- **GIVEN** a Go module is initialized\n- **WHEN** the directory structure is created\n- **THEN** the pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1 directory SHALL exist\n- **AND** the pkg/client directory SHALL exist\n- **AND** the pkg/informers directory SHALL exist\n- **AND** the pkg/listers directory SHALL exist\n\n### Requirement: API types definition\n\nThe system SHALL define API types for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter with proper Kubernetes markers.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime type definition\n- **GIVEN** the pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go file\n- **WHEN** the AgentRuntime type is defined\n- **THEN** the type SHALL have apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n- **AND** the type SHALL have kind: AgentRuntime\n- **AND** the type SHALL have Spec and Status fields\n- **AND** the type SHALL have JSON tags\n- **AND** the type SHALL have kubebuilder validation tags\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type definition\n- **GIVEN** the pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go file\n- **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter type is defined\n- **THEN** the type SHALL have apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n- **AND** the type SHALL have kind: CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** the type SHALL have Spec and Status fields\n- **AND** the type SHALL have JSON tags\n- **AND** the type SHALL have kubebuilder validation tags\n\n#### Scenario: API registration\n- **GIVEN** the pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go file\n- **WHEN** API types are registered\n- **THEN** the SchemeBuilder SHALL register AgentRuntime\n- **AND** the SchemeBuilder SHALL register CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** the GroupName SHALL be runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n- **AND** the SchemeGroupVersion SHALL be runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n\n### Requirement: Code generation configuration\n\nThe system SHALL configure code-generator to generate client, informer, and lister code.\n\n#### Scenario: client-gen configuration\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile with client-gen target\n- **WHEN** the generate target is executed\n- **THEN** client-gen SHALL generate clientset code\n- **AND** the clientset SHALL be in pkg/client/clientset/versioned\n- **AND** the clientset SHALL include AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter clients\n\n#### Scenario: informer-gen configuration\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile with informer-gen target\n- **WHEN** the generate target is executed\n- **THEN** informer-gen SHALL generate informer code\n- **AND** the informers SHALL be in pkg/informers/externalversions\n- **AND** the informers SHALL include AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter informers\n\n#### Scenario: lister-gen configuration\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile with lister-gen target\n- **WHEN** the generate target is executed\n- **THEN** lister-gen SHALL generate lister code\n- **AND** the listers SHALL be in pkg/listers\n- **AND** the listers SHALL include AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter listers\n\n### Requirement: ClientSet API\n\nThe system SHALL provide a complete ClientSet API for managing AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources.\n\n#### Scenario: ClientSet initialization\n- **GIVEN** a valid kubeconfig file\n- **WHEN** a ClientSet is created using clientcmd.BuildConfigFromFlags\n- **THEN** the ClientSet SHALL be initialized successfully\n- **AND** the ClientSet SHALL have a Runtime() method\n- **AND** the ClientSet SHALL have a Discovery() method\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Create operation\n- **GIVEN** a valid AgentRuntime object\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Create is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be created in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the created AgentRuntime\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Get operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime name\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return the AgentRuntime object\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n- **AND** the method SHALL return error if AgentRuntime does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime List operation\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with AgentRuntimes\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).List is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an AgentRuntimeList\n- **AND** the list SHALL contain all AgentRuntimes in the namespace\n- **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n- **AND** the method SHALL support field selector filtering\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Update operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime object\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Update is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the updated AgentRuntime\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime UpdateStatus operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime object\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).UpdateStatus is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime status SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the updated AgentRuntime\n- **AND** the method SHALL not modify the spec\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Delete operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime name\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Delete is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be deleted from Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Watch operation\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Watch is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return a watch.Interface\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Add events for new AgentRuntimes\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Update events for modified AgentRuntimes\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Delete events for deleted AgentRuntimes\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime Patch operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime object\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Patch is called\n- **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be patched in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL support JSON patch type\n- **AND** the method SHALL support Merge patch type\n- **AND** the method SHALL support Strategic merge patch type\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Create operation\n- **GIVEN** a valid CodeInterpreter object\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Create is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be created in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the created CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Get operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter name\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return the CodeInterpreter object\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n- **AND** the method SHALL return error if CodeInterpreter does not exist\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter List operation\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster with CodeInterpreters\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).List is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return a CodeInterpreterList\n- **AND** the list SHALL contain all CodeInterpreters in the namespace\n- **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n- **AND** the method SHALL support field selector filtering\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Update operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter object\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Update is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the updated CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter UpdateStatus operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter object\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).UpdateStatus is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter status SHALL be updated in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return the updated CodeInterpreter\n- **AND** the method SHALL not modify the spec\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Delete operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter name\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Delete is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be deleted from Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL return nil error on success\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Watch operation\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Watch is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return a watch.Interface\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Add events for new CodeInterpreters\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Update events for modified CodeInterpreters\n- **AND** the watch SHALL receive Delete events for deleted CodeInterpreters\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter Patch operation\n- **GIVEN** an existing CodeInterpreter object\n- **WHEN** client.Runtime().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Patch is called\n- **THEN** the CodeInterpreter SHALL be patched in Kubernetes\n- **AND** the method SHALL support JSON patch type\n- **AND** the method SHALL support Merge patch type\n- **AND** the method SHALL support Strategic merge patch type\n\n### Requirement: Informer API\n\nThe system SHALL provide informer support for event-driven workflows.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime informer setup\n- **GIVEN** a ClientSet\n- **WHEN** an AgentRuntime informer is created\n- **THEN** the informer SHALL watch for AgentRuntime changes\n- **AND** the informer SHALL maintain a local cache\n- **AND** the informer SHALL provide a Lister for read-only access\n\n#### Scenario: Informer event handler registration\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer\n- **WHEN** event handlers are registered\n- **THEN** the AddFunc SHALL be called when AgentRuntimes are added\n- **AND** the UpdateFunc SHALL be called when AgentRuntimes are updated\n- **AND** the DeleteFunc SHALL be called when AgentRuntimes are deleted\n\n#### Scenario: Informer cache synchronization\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer\n- **WHEN** the informer is started\n- **THEN** the cache SHALL synchronize with Kubernetes\n- **AND** the cache SHALL contain all existing AgentRuntimes\n- **AND** the cache SHALL be updated on changes\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter informer setup\n- **GIVEN** a ClientSet\n- **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter informer is created\n- **THEN** the informer SHALL watch for CodeInterpreter changes\n- **AND** the informer SHALL maintain a local cache\n- **AND** the informer SHALL provide a Lister for read-only access\n\n### Requirement: Lister API\n\nThe system SHALL provide lister support for efficient read-only operations.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime lister operations\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime informer with synchronized cache\n- **WHEN** the lister.List method is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return all AgentRuntimes in the cache\n- **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n- **AND** the method SHALL be O(1) for individual lookups\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime namespace lister\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime lister\n- **WHEN** AgentRuntimes(namespace) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return a namespace-scoped lister\n- **AND** the namespace lister SHALL only return AgentRuntimes in that namespace\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter lister operations\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter informer with synchronized cache\n- **WHEN** the lister.List method is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return all CodeInterpreters in the cache\n- **AND** the method SHALL support label selector filtering\n- **AND** the method SHALL be O(1) for individual lookups\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter namespace lister\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter lister\n- **WHEN** CodeInterpreters(namespace) is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return a namespace-scoped lister\n- **AND** the namespace lister SHALL only return CodeInterpreters in that namespace\n\n### Requirement: Error handling\n\nThe system SHALL provide proper error handling for all client operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Not found error\n- **GIVEN** a non-existent resource name\n- **WHEN** a Get operation is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n- **AND** the error SHALL be of type *errors.StatusError\n- **AND** the error status code SHALL be 404\n\n#### Scenario: Already exists error\n- **GIVEN** an existing resource name\n- **WHEN** a Create operation is called with the same name\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n- **AND** the error SHALL be of type *errors.StatusError\n- **AND** the error status code SHALL be 409\n\n#### Scenario: Permission denied error\n- **GIVEN** a client with insufficient permissions\n- **WHEN** an operation is called\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n- **AND** the error SHALL be of type *errors.StatusError\n- **AND** the error status code SHALL be 403\n\n#### Scenario: Context cancellation\n- **GIVEN** a context that is cancelled\n- **WHEN** an operation is called with the cancelled context\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n- **AND** the error SHALL be context.Canceled\n\n#### Scenario: Timeout error\n- **GIVEN** a context with a timeout\n- **WHEN** an operation takes longer than the timeout\n- **THEN** the method SHALL return an error\n- **AND** the error SHALL be context.DeadlineExceeded\n\n### Requirement: Type safety\n\nThe system SHALL provide type-safe API access through Go types.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime type safety\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime object\n- **WHEN** the object is passed to client methods\n- **THEN** the methods SHALL accept only AgentRuntime type\n- **AND** the methods SHALL return AgentRuntime type\n- **AND** compile-time type checking SHALL be enforced\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type safety\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter object\n- **WHEN** the object is passed to client methods\n- **THEN** the methods SHALL accept only CodeInterpreter type\n- **AND** the methods SHALL return CodeInterpreter type\n- **AND** compile-time type checking SHALL be enforced\n\n### Requirement: Testing\n\nThe system SHALL include comprehensive tests for all functionality.\n\n#### Scenario: Unit tests for client methods\n- **GIVEN** the client code\n- **WHEN** unit tests are run\n- **THEN** all Create, Update, Get, List, Delete methods SHALL be tested\n- **AND** all error cases SHALL be tested\n- **AND** test coverage SHALL be at least 80%\n\n#### Scenario: Unit tests for informer\n- **GIVEN** the informer code\n- **WHEN** unit tests are run\n- **THEN** informer initialization SHALL be tested\n- **AND** event handling SHALL be tested\n- **AND** cache operations SHALL be tested\n\n#### Scenario: Unit tests for lister\n- **GIVEN** the lister code\n- **WHEN** unit tests are run\n- **THEN** list operations SHALL be tested\n- **AND** namespace filtering SHALL be tested\n- **AND** selector filtering SHALL be tested\n\n#### Scenario: Integration tests\n- **GIVEN** a Kubernetes cluster\n- **WHEN** integration tests are run\n- **THEN** all client operations SHALL be tested against real cluster\n- **AND** watch functionality SHALL be tested\n- **AND** informer synchronization SHALL be tested\n\n### Requirement: Documentation\n\nThe system SHALL include comprehensive documentation for all APIs.\n\n#### Scenario: README documentation\n- **GIVEN** the client-go repository\n- **WHEN** README.md is reviewed\n- **THEN** installation instructions SHALL be provided\n- **AND** basic usage examples SHALL be provided\n- **AND** API reference SHALL be provided\n\n#### Scenario: API documentation\n- **GIVEN** the client API\n- **WHEN** documentation is reviewed\n- **THEN** all public methods SHALL be documented\n- **AND** all parameters SHALL be documented\n- **AND** all return values SHALL be documented\n- **AND** error cases SHALL be documented\n\n#### Scenario: Usage examples\n- **GIVEN** the examples directory\n- **WHEN** examples are reviewed\n- **THEN** clientset usage examples SHALL be provided\n- **AND** informer usage examples SHALL be provided\n- **AND** lister usage examples SHALL be provided\n\n### Requirement: Code generation automation\n\nThe system SHALL automate code generation to keep it in sync with CRD definitions.\n\n#### Scenario: Makefile generate target\n- **GIVEN** the Makefile\n- **WHEN** `make generate` is executed\n- **THEN** client-gen SHALL run\n- **AND** informer-gen SHALL run\n- **AND** lister-gen SHALL run\n- **AND** all generated code SHALL be up to date\n\n#### Scenario: CI code generation check\n- **GIVEN** a CI pipeline\n- **WHEN** code is committed\n- **THEN** the CI SHALL check if generated code is up to date\n- **AND** the CI SHALL fail if generated code is out of date\n\n---\n\n## Backward Compatibility\n\nThis delta specification defines a new Go module for the client-go client library. The module provides a new API for accessing AgentCube resources and does not affect existing deployments. Existing code using direct REST API calls can continue to work, but it is recommended to migrate to the typed client for better type safety and developer experience.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nThis delta specification depends on:\n- Go 1.19+\n- Kubernetes 1.20+\n- AR-001: Core API definitions (CRDs)\n- AR-002: AgentRuntime CRD definition\n- AR-003: CodeInterpreter CRD definition\n- k8s.io/code-generator\n- k8s.io/client-go\n\n## Breaking Changes\n\nNone. This delta specification defines a new Go module that provides a client library. It does not break any existing functionality.\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n1. **Authentication**: The client shall support all Kubernetes authentication methods (kubeconfig, service account tokens, TLS certificates).\n2. **Authorization**: The client shall respect Kubernetes RBAC policies and shall fail with appropriate errors when permissions are insufficient.\n3. **Secret Handling**: The client shall not log sensitive information such as tokens or passwords.\n4. **TLS Verification**: The client shall verify server TLS certificates by default.\n5. **Context Security**: The client shall respect context cancellation and timeouts to prevent resource leaks.\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n- Test all client methods (Create, Update, Get, List, Delete, Watch, Patch)\n- Test error handling for all error cases\n- Test informer initialization and event handling\n- Test lister operations and filtering\n\n### Integration Tests\n- Test all client operations against a real Kubernetes cluster\n- Test watch functionality with real events\n- Test informer synchronization\n- Test concurrent operations\n\n### Performance Tests\n- Test CRUD operation latency\n- Test list operation latency with many resources\n- Test watch operation latency\n- Test informer cache synchronization time\n- Test memory usage with large numbers of resources\n\n### Compatibility Tests\n- Test against multiple Kubernetes versions (1.20, 1.21, 1.22, 1.23, 1.24)\n- Test with different API server configurations\n- Test with different authentication methods","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-035/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775886947261,"end":1775886947268}}}}
